added.title: Craig of the Campus
added.description: Craig is dragged along on a college tour, but quickly finds himself chasing after a creek legend.

added.title: Wheels Collide
added.description: Craig tries to bring together the fastest kids in the Creek, and accidentally creates a rivalry between the 10 Speeds and the Roller Derby Kids.

added.title: The Magical Box
added.description: After Grizz, Panda and Ice Bear receive a special box, the brothers discover its magical ability to transport them anywhere in the universe.

added.title: Bears and the Beanstalk
added.description: The Bears work as short-order cooks in a giant's diner.

added.title: Boo-Dunnit
added.description: When the box goes missing at a haunted mansion, the Bears play detective to help uncover the thief.

added.title: The Little Mer-Bear
added.description: In order to live under the sea the Bears must transform into mermaids.

added.title: Wiggin' Out
added.description: Bridgette donates her hair to a charity that makes wigs for hairless cats and now some classmates want to do the same. But their quest for perfect wig hair drives them to weird and dangerous lengths.

added.title: The Upside of Hunger
added.description: Owen has a mishap while baking an upside-down cake and is transported to an upside-down world where he is forced to outwit himself in order to get his cake back.

added.title: Fire in the Hole
added.description: Duncan cooks up a nuclear hot sauce to mess with Chef, but accidentally summons Terry Spice, King of the Underworld!

added.title: Tu Ba or Not Tu Ba
added.description: The class tries to help Chef achieve his dream of joining the world's most famous Tuba Band, Tubalicious, only to regret it when they realize how much they'll miss him.

added.title: Dude Where's Macaw
added.description: While trying to defend his elite gamer status Chef uses an old cheat code that brings a dangerous avatar to life.

added.title: Players of the Lost Park
added.description: When Team Tennyson visits Raspberry Park for some R & R, they get more than they bargained for. What they think are innocent games of chance are a revenge plot by Zombozo to steal the Rustbuggy and rob Team Tennyson!

added.title: De-Fanged!
added.description: Team Tennyson travels to the new Laser Town VR, but when Kevin cheats his way to the top, Ben must team up with former champ Fang if he is going to defeat his souped-up rival.

added.title: Mock 10
added.description: Ben, Kevin and La Grange find themselves stuck 'outside of time' after the latter hijacks a supersonic train with a faulty engine, forcing the trio to team up and slow down.

added.title: Rekoil
added.description: As Team Tennyson fights to stop Dr. Animo from raiding an animal shelter, Ben faces one villain more than he bargained for, King Koil, now Animo's pet.

added.title: Buktu The Future
added.description: After Tim Buktu's live stream is mysteriously cut short, Team Tennyson must attempt a rescue mission and break inside the highly confidential Area 55 in order to save him.

added.title: Under Wraps
added.description: When Ben and Gwen are sent to a farm to learn the value of hard work, what they really learn is that an evil alien mummy has arrived on Earth.

added.title: The Unnaturals
added.description: Ben learns that evil robots have replaced all the kids at the Little League World Series. And now they want to replace the President of the USA!

added.title: The Return
added.description: Ghostfreak has returned! And he has brought a Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein like aliens with him to help him shroud the Earth in darkness.

added.title: Be Afraid of the Dark
added.description: Ben travels into space to thwart Ghostfreak's diabolical plans. But is he hero enough to take on the Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein?

added.title: The Visitor
added.description: A mysterious alien named Xylene shows up and wants to return the Omnitrix to its rightful owner, Grandpa Max!

added.title: The Skull Sorcerer
added.description: Separated from the others, Cole must trust his instincts and make the right choices to find his way to the surface to alert King Vangelis of the dangerous Skull Sorcerer.

added.title: The Real Fall!
added.description: An entire episode chronicles the ninja's most bizarre adventure yet: in which Cole, Princess Vania and Master Wu fall down a seemingly endless tunnel, into the bowels of Shintaro Mountain.

added.title: Dungeon Party
added.description: Having survived their fall into the mountain, Cole, Wu and Princess Vania befriend a motley group of survivors, called the Lowly, and are told the story of how they too ended up at "Rock-Bottom."

added.title: Dungeon Crawl!
added.description: Having joined forces with the Lowly in their quest to defeat King Vangelis, Cole, Wu, and Vania have to find a way out of the bottom of the mountain, a place said to be inescapable.

added.title: Grief Bringer
added.description: Nya and Kai, who have become the respective leaders of the Munce and Geckles, attempt to unite the tribes in an effort to defeat their mutual enemy, the Skull Sorcerer, who schemes against them.

added.title: Un Dia Peludo
added.description: Bridgette dona su cabello a una organización benéfica que fabrica pelucas para gatos sin pelo y ahora algunos compañeros quieren hacer lo mismo. Pero su búsqueda de una peluca perfecta los lleva a longitudes extrañas y peligrosas.

added.title: El Hechicero Calavera
added.description: Separado de los demás, Cole debe encontrar su camino a la superficie para advertir al Rey Vangelis sobre el peligroso Hechicero Calavera.

added.title: La Gran Caida
added.description: Este episodio relata cómo Cole, la princesa Vania y el maestro Wu caen por un túnel aparentemente interminable, dentro de la montaña de Shintaro.

added.title: Fiesta en el Calabozo
added.description: Cole, Wu y la Princesa Vania conocen a un grupo de sobrevivientes llamados los de abajo, ellos cuentan cómo terminaron en "Lo más profundo".

added.title: El Camino en el Calabozo
added.description: En su misión de derrotar al Rey Vangelis, Cole, Wu y Vania unen fuerzas con "Los de abajo" para encontrar una forma de salir del fondo de la montaña.

added.title: El Dragon Grief-Bringer
added.description: Nya y Kai, quienes se han convertido en los líderes de los Munces y Geckles, intentan unirlos para derrotar a su enemigo mutuo, el Hechicero Calavera.

added.title: El Reves del Hambre
added.description: Owen tiene un percance mientras horneaba un pastel al revés y es transportado a un mundo al revés donde se ve obligado a burlarse de sí mismo para recuperar su pastel.

added.title: Y Donde Esta el Guacamayo?
added.description: Mientras intenta defender su estatus de jugador de élite, Chef usa un antiguo código de trampa que da vida a un avatar peligroso.

added.title: Tuba o No Tuba
added.description: La clase intenta ayudar al Chef a lograr su sueño de unirse a la banda de tuba más famosa del mundo, Tubalicious, solo para arrepentirse cuando se dan cuenta de cuánto lo extrañarán.

added.title: Dino Fright
added.description: George P. Mandrake hires The Looney Builders to build a T. Rex fossil. It's Tweety's job to place the bones with his crane, but his fear of the big dino affects his ability to get the job done.

added.title: Snow Cap
added.description: Pauleen Penguin hires The Looney Builders to build her a home in Looneyburg. Lola soon discovers they got the design wrong and the crew has to make adjustments.

added.title: Picture Perfect Park Party/Sun Block
added.description: Hero Celebration Day is finishing with a slideshow of everyday heroes, that is, until the projector screen rips./Pretty Big City is cooling off with an ice slide in the park, but the situation gets slippery when the slide starts melting.

added.title: Roll Chickens, Roll!/Ramp Up, Up, And Away
added.description: Farmer MacBarm is hosting the Sunny Field Farm Chicken Roll, but the race gets off to a slow start when the chickens don't roll./Ranger Nat can't wait to see Pinecone's Comet, that is, until his telescope falls to the bottom of a cliff.
